cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about salient object detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel architecture design for the saliency inference module, which involves deep learning techniques. Hence, it is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the computational cost of the proposed method, indicating a potential interest in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experiments with image datasets, suggesting a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
